Well, nobody's perfect.

970
01:22:52,397 --> 01:22:56,151
What's the last thing
that you do remember?

971
01:22:59,320 --> 01:23:01,406
- My wife.
- That's sweet.

972
01:23:01,489 --> 01:23:02,365
Dying.

973
01:23:04,284 --> 01:23:06,745
l remember my wife dying.

974
01:23:10,457 --> 01:23:13,293
Let me, um, get you another one.

975
01:23:13,376 --> 01:23:15,336
l think this one's dusty.

976
01:23:19,591 --> 01:23:22,510
Why are you calling me?
What do you want?

977
01:23:22,594 --> 01:23:26,139
l know you're a cop. What do you want?
Have l done something wrong?

978
01:23:26,431 --> 01:23:28,808
l don't know, something bad, maybe.

979
01:23:30,310 --> 01:23:32,771
Look, why are you asking me?
l can't remember what I've done.

980
01:23:32,854 --> 01:23:34,898
You wouldn't believe me anyway.

981
01:23:34,939 --> 01:23:37,942
Because of my condition, you don't
believe someone with this condition.

982
01:23:38,026 --> 01:23:40,737
Nobody believed Sammy!
l didn't even fucking believe Sammy!

983
01:23:41,488 --> 01:23:43,531
Ferdy's bar.

984
01:23:45,700 --> 01:23:48,244
Come by after. Natalie.

985
01:24:03,176 --> 01:24:05,136
- A beer, please.
- What do you want?

986
01:24:05,220 --> 01:24:06,221
A beer, please.

987
01:24:06,304 --> 01:24:08,682
You can't just waltz in here
dressed like that and ask for a beer.

988
01:24:08,765 --> 01:24:11,101
- What, is there a dress code?
- Why are you here?

989
01:24:11,226 --> 01:24:14,229
- I'm meeting someone called Natalie.
- Well, that's me.

990
01:24:14,312 --> 01:24:16,981
Yeah, we met before, right?

991
01:24:17,857 --> 01:24:20,110
- Then why am l here?
- l don't know, why don't you tell me?

992
01:24:20,193 --> 01:24:22,237
l don't remember.
l have no short-term memory.

993
01:24:22,320 --> 01:24:24,072
Oh, you're that memory guy.

994
01:24:24,197 --> 01:24:27,951
- How do you know about me?
- My boyfriend told me about you.

995
01:24:28,034 --> 01:24:31,955
- Oh, yeah? Who's your boyfriend?
- Jimmy Grants. Do you know him?

996
01:24:33,164 --> 01:24:34,541
No.

997
01:24:34,624 --> 01:24:39,963
He knows you. He told me about you.
He said you were staying at the Discount.

998
01:24:40,130 --> 01:24:43,383
In fact, a cop came by earlier
and was looking for you.

999
01:24:43,466 --> 01:24:45,593
Said he was looking for a guy
who can't remember anything,...

1000
01:24:45,677 --> 01:24:47,721
...wouldn't know how he'd got here
or what he'd done.

1001
01:24:47,804 --> 01:24:49,723
l get a lot of guys round here like that.

1002
01:24:49,806 --> 01:24:54,269
Chronic alcoholism
is one cause of short-term memory loss.

1003
01:24:55,937 --> 01:24:59,065
- Are you Teddy?
- No, my name's Leonard.

1004
01:24:59,149 --> 01:25:01,276
- Did Teddy send you?
- l don't know.

1005
01:25:01,901 --> 01:25:03,945
What's happened to Jimmy?

1006
01:25:04,029 --> 01:25:07,741
- l don't know that, either. Sorry.
- You don't remember anything?

1007
01:25:07,824 --> 01:25:11,453
You don't remember where you've been
or what you've just done?

1008
01:25:11,536 --> 01:25:14,956
l can't make new memories.
Everything just fades.

1009
01:25:15,081 --> 01:25:17,876
- Then why did you come here?
- l found this in my pocket.

1010
01:25:21,171 --> 01:25:23,298
Your pocket?

1011
01:25:38,438 --> 01:25:39,939
(man hawks)

1012
01:25:47,655 --> 01:25:50,492
Bar bet. Care to contribute?

1013
01:25:50,575 --> 01:25:53,036
- No, thanks.
- It's for a lot of money.

1014
01:25:53,453 --> 01:25:57,374
Come on. Proceeds are going to charity.
Help me out.

1015
01:26:02,670 --> 01:26:04,672
(hawks)

1016
01:26:08,718 --> 01:26:10,512
Thank you.

1017
01:26:27,445 --> 01:26:30,490
- On the house.
- Thanks.

1018
01:26:31,366 --> 01:26:33,410
(man laughs)

1019
01:26:34,369 --> 01:26:37,872
It's completely fucked
because nobody believes you.

1020
01:26:37,914 --> 01:26:41,626
It's amazing what a little brain damage
will do for your credibility.

1021
01:26:41,710 --> 01:26:44,045
l guess it's poetic justice
for not believing Sammy.

1022
01:26:44,129 --> 01:26:48,925
You know the truth about my condition,
officer? You don't know anything.

1023
01:26:49,008 --> 01:26:54,097
You feel angry, you don't know why.
You feel guilty, you have no idea why.

1024
01:26:54,180 --> 01:26:57,642
You could do anything and not have
the faintest idea ten minutes later.

1025
01:26:57,767 --> 01:27:00,729
Like Sammy.
What if I'd done something like Sammy?

1026
01:27:00,812 --> 01:27:04,733
l didn't tell you?
What happened to Sammy and his wife?

1027
01:27:04,816 --> 01:27:06,985
She came to see me at my office.

1028
01:27:07,068 --> 01:27:11,948
l didn't tell her what l really thought
but l never said that he was faking.

1029
01:27:12,115 --> 01:27:14,325
Just that his condition was mental,
not physical.

1030
01:27:14,451 --> 01:27:17,037
l found out later that she went home
and gave Sammy his final exam.

1031
01:27:18,913 --> 01:27:21,708
Sammy? It's time for my shot.

1032
01:27:37,724 --> 01:27:40,810
She knew beyond a doubt
that he loved her,

1033
01:27:40,894 --> 01:27:43,563
so she found a way to test him.

1034
01:27:55,575 --> 01:27:59,162
Sammy? It's time for my shot.

1035
01:28:00,121 --> 01:28:02,165
Hm.

1036
01:28:09,422 --> 01:28:13,218
- She really thought she'd call his bluff.
- There you go.

1037
01:28:13,301 --> 01:28:17,972
Or she just didn't want to live with
the things she'd put him through.

1038
01:28:26,731 --> 01:28:28,108
Sammy?

1039
01:28:30,318 --> 01:28:31,736
It's time for my shot.

1040
01:28:37,909 --> 01:28:39,661
It won't hurt.

1041
01:29:23,496 --> 01:29:26,791
She went into a coma
and never recovered.

1042
01:29:26,916 --> 01:29:30,253
Sammy couldn't understand
or explain what happened.

1043
01:29:30,336 --> 01:29:31,337
Oh!

1044
01:29:32,464 --> 01:29:36,843
He's been in a home ever since.
He doesn't even know his wife is dead.

1045
01:29:36,926 --> 01:29:40,305
l was wrong about Sammy
and l was wrong about his wife.

1046
01:29:40,430 --> 01:29:44,517
She wasn't interested in the money.
She needed to understand his problem.

1047
01:29:44,684 --> 01:29:48,396
His brain didn't respond to conditioning
but he wasn't a con man.

1048
01:29:48,438 --> 01:29:51,816
And when she looked into his eyes,
she thought he could be the same person.

1049
01:29:51,941 --> 01:29:54,027
When l looked into his eyes,
l thought l saw recognition.

1050
01:29:54,110 --> 01:29:56,154
Now l know you fake it.

1051
01:29:56,237 --> 01:29:59,324
lf you think you're supposed to recognize
somebody, you pretend to.

1052
01:29:59,407 --> 01:30:02,952
You bluff it to get a pat on the head
from the doctors.

1053
01:30:03,036 --> 01:30:06,122
You bluff it to seem less of a freak.

1054
01:30:07,874 --> 01:30:09,918
What drug dealer?

1055
01:30:10,710 --> 01:30:12,796
(tires squeal)

1056
01:30:35,527 --> 01:30:38,613
- Hey, Lenny, how you doing?
- It's private back here.

1057
01:30:38,697 --> 01:30:41,700
- It's OK, we know each other. Right, kid?
- How did you know l was in here?

1058
01:30:41,783 --> 01:30:43,785
The Jag's out front.

1059
01:30:43,868 --> 01:30:46,871
What are you still doing here, Lenny?
There's plenty of tattoo parlors up north.

1060
01:30:46,955 --> 01:30:50,500
l guess l wanted to get something down
before it slipped my mind.

1061
01:30:50,583 --> 01:30:52,544
- Give me the keys, I'll move it.
- It'll be all right.

1062
01:30:52,627 --> 01:30:54,671
- Wait out there.
- Oh, for Christ...

1063
01:30:54,754 --> 01:30:56,840
Give me a minute,
I've got to get something for you.

1064
01:31:01,511 --> 01:31:05,056
Fact six. Car license SG137IU.

1065
01:31:11,396 --> 01:31:14,524
Look, wait a minute, will ya?

1066
01:31:17,152 --> 01:31:19,404
- We gotta get you out of here.
- Why?

1067
01:31:19,529 --> 01:31:22,449
Oh, man. Come on, Leonard.
How many times l gotta tell you?

1068
01:31:22,532 --> 01:31:25,076
- It's not safe for you to hang around.
- Why not?

1069
01:31:25,160 --> 01:31:28,413
Because that cop's looking for you.
l gotta get you a new identity,...

1070
01:31:28,496 --> 01:31:31,875
...some new clothes, a different car
would do for now. Put these on.

1071
01:31:31,958 --> 01:31:33,835
Whoa, whoa. What cop?

1072
01:31:33,918 --> 01:31:38,006
He's a bad cop. He's the one
that checked you into the Discount Inn.

1073
01:31:38,089 --> 01:31:42,052
He's been calling you for days, slipping
envelopes under your door, shit like that.

1074
01:31:42,135 --> 01:31:46,139
- How do you know this?
- He told me. He's been laughing at you.

1075
01:31:46,222 --> 01:31:47,682
- You're full of shit.
- No, I'm not.

1076
01:31:47,766 --> 01:31:49,809
He knows you're no good on the phone
so he's been calling you up.

1077
01:31:49,893 --> 01:31:51,853
Sometimes you don't answer the phone...

1078
01:31:51,978 --> 01:31:54,731
...so he slips shit under your door
to scare you into answering it,...

1079
01:31:54,856 --> 01:31:59,944
...giving you a line of crap about John G
being a local drug dealer. Jimmy Grants.

1080
01:32:00,153 --> 01:32:02,864
- Who's Jimmy Grants?
- Leonard, Jimmy's the drug dealer.

1081
01:32:02,947 --> 01:32:06,493
The cop wants to know how his operation
is run. He's got some score in mind.

1082
01:32:06,576 --> 01:32:09,079
- Somehow you're involved.
- How do you know him?

1083
01:32:09,162 --> 01:32:14,834
I'm a snitch. He's a cop from out of town.
The local boys put us together.

1084
01:32:15,001 --> 01:32:17,295
lf he knew l was helping you,
he'd fucking kill me.

1085
01:32:17,379 --> 01:32:21,174
So take these clothes, put them on
and get the fuck out of here.

1086
01:32:21,257 --> 01:32:23,134
Come on, Leonard, just go.

1087
01:32:43,446 --> 01:32:45,365
You are full of shit.

1088
01:32:48,201 --> 01:32:50,328
Come by after. Natalie.

1089
01:32:50,954 --> 01:32:52,831
Ferdy's bar.

1090
01:33:33,246 --> 01:33:34,622
(knocks on window)

1091
01:33:34,789 --> 01:33:36,958
Hey, Jimmy.

1092
01:33:38,543 --> 01:33:41,629
I'm sorry, l, uh,
thought you were somebody else.

1093
01:33:42,005 --> 01:33:43,840
Sorry.

1094
01:33:43,923 --> 01:33:45,967
That's OK.

1095
01:33:59,773 --> 01:34:03,818
This Jimmy Grants deals drugs
out of the bar where his girlfriend works?

1096
01:34:04,194 --> 01:34:07,947
But he's not going to bring her along?
He'll come by himself, right?

1097
01:34:07,989 --> 01:34:11,951
l always figured the drugs angle
would be the best way to get him.

1098
01:34:12,160 --> 01:34:15,497
No, officer. I'm as ready as I'll ever be.

1099
01:34:15,580 --> 01:34:18,541
You're in the lobby?
What do you look like?

1100
01:34:19,793 --> 01:34:20,752
I'll be right there.

1101
01:35:03,920 --> 01:35:04,838
Lenny!

1102
01:35:07,090 --> 01:35:09,134
Officer Gammell?

1103
01:35:12,137 --> 01:35:14,180
Yeah. Come on.

1104
01:35:30,905 --> 01:35:33,950
- Hey, smile.
- Oh, don't, uh... Not here.

1105
01:35:34,784 --> 01:35:36,786
Over here.

1106
01:35:41,332 --> 01:35:43,960
Is it Officer or Lieutenant Gammell?

1107
01:35:44,044 --> 01:35:47,047
You know what?
Don't write Gammell, just Teddy.

1108
01:35:47,130 --> 01:35:49,799
- Why?
- I'm undercover.

1109
01:35:52,427 --> 01:35:55,263
This is the directions, where he's going.

1110
01:35:55,347 --> 01:35:58,224
- My number's on the bottom if you...
- You're not coming?

1111
01:35:58,308 --> 01:36:01,061
Nah, it wouldn't be appropriate.

1112
01:36:04,981 --> 01:36:07,650
Nice picture. l look thin.

1113
01:36:10,445 --> 01:36:11,821
Hey, Lenny!

1114
01:36:13,406 --> 01:36:14,783
Make him beg.

1115
01:37:37,449 --> 01:37:39,492
Teddy!

1116
01:37:41,619 --> 01:37:42,787
Hey, Teddy!

1117
01:37:45,832 --> 01:37:47,709
Teddy!

1118
01:37:50,879 --> 01:37:52,672
Jimmy.

1119
01:37:53,173 --> 01:37:56,426
- What the fuck are you doing here?
- You Jimmy Grants?

1120
01:37:56,509 --> 01:37:58,470
Expecting any other Jimmies,
memory man?

1121
01:37:58,553 --> 01:38:02,807
- Do you remember me?
- Yeah, l remember you.

1122
01:38:02,891 --> 01:38:05,310
Where the fuck's Teddy?

1123
01:38:05,393 --> 01:38:06,478
Well?

1124
01:38:10,148 --> 01:38:12,025
Motherfuck!

1125
01:38:12,150 --> 01:38:12,942
What are you doing?

1126
01:38:15,111 --> 01:38:16,363
Strip.

1127
01:38:16,446 --> 01:38:18,907
- You're making a big fucking mistake!
- Strip!

1128
01:38:20,450 --> 01:38:23,536
My associates are not the kind of people
you wanna piss off.

1129
01:38:23,620 --> 01:38:25,330
Don't say anything else.

1130
01:38:25,372 --> 01:38:28,416
- l knew l couldn't trust that fuck!
- Take it off.

1131
01:38:33,755 --> 01:38:35,799
Your pants, too.

1132
01:38:35,965 --> 01:38:38,343
- Why?
- l don't wanna get blood on them.

1133
01:38:38,468 --> 01:38:42,430
Whoa, whoa, whoa! Wait, wait, wait!
Did he tell you what l was bringing?

1134
01:38:42,514 --> 01:38:46,518
- Take your fuckin' pants off!
- I've got two hundred grand in the car!

1135
01:38:46,601 --> 01:38:49,312
- Just take it!
- You think you can bargain with me?

1136
01:38:49,396 --> 01:38:51,690
- Just take the money and walk away.
- l don't want your fucking money.

1137
01:38:51,773 --> 01:38:54,192
Then, what?

1138
01:38:54,275 --> 01:38:57,529
- What do you want from me?
- l want my fucking life back!

1139
01:40:29,037 --> 01:40:30,205
(softly) Sammy.

1140
01:40:37,045 --> 01:40:39,172
He said Sammy.
How does he know about Sammy?

1141
01:40:39,255 --> 01:40:41,299
Oh, fuck.

1142
01:41:01,152 --> 01:41:03,196
What have l done?

1143
01:41:04,531 --> 01:41:05,699
Hey, mister! l need help!

1144
01:41:05,824 --> 01:41:09,327
There's a guy in here, he's hurt bad.
We gotta get him to a doctor.

1145
01:41:09,411 --> 01:41:10,620
All right.

1146
01:41:11,913 --> 01:41:14,165
l don't know what happened.
I've got this memory thing.

1147
01:41:14,249 --> 01:41:17,210
- Do l know you?
- No. Don't worry, I'm a cop.

1148
01:41:17,293 --> 01:41:20,588
- Is he still breathing?
- Well, l don't know. Maybe.

1149
01:41:20,672 --> 01:41:25,677
- What the hell were you guys doing?
- l don't remember, l have this condition.

1150
01:41:25,760 --> 01:41:28,763
l hope it's not as serious as his
cos this guy's dead.

1151
01:41:29,222 --> 01:41:33,143
- Ow! Lenny! That shit kills!
- So you remember me now, huh?

1152
01:41:33,184 --> 01:41:37,856
- You are a fucking cop!
- And I'm the guy that helped you find him.

1153
01:41:37,939 --> 01:41:42,360
- Get up! Get up!
- Lenny, you got the wrong idea!

1154
01:41:45,321 --> 01:41:47,407
Who is that? He knew me.

1155
01:41:47,490 --> 01:41:50,118
Of course he did, he raped your wife,
he fucked up your brain.

1156
01:41:50,201 --> 01:41:52,245
Bullshit! He's not the guy.

1157
01:41:52,328 --> 01:41:56,166
His name is James F Grants. John G.
Check your tattoos.

1158
01:41:56,291 --> 01:41:59,002
- Why did he bring two hundred grand?
- What?

1159
01:42:01,004 --> 01:42:03,298
- What was it for?
- Amphetamines l told him l had.

1160
01:42:03,381 --> 01:42:06,885
- Is this a drug deal?
- No. Yeah, that and your thing.

1161
01:42:07,052 --> 01:42:10,555
Look, Jimmy's your guy. l figured
we'd make a few dollars on the side.

1162
01:42:10,638 --> 01:42:13,516
- How did he know me?
- The Discount Inn.

1163
01:42:13,600 --> 01:42:17,979
He dealt out of there. The guy at the front
desk let him know if anybody came round.

1164
01:42:18,104 --> 01:42:20,357
He called Jimmy
the minute he saw you taking a picture.

1165
01:42:20,440 --> 01:42:22,901
- You're fucking using me.
- No! You get half.

1166
01:42:22,984 --> 01:42:25,445
He knew about Sammy,
why would l tell him about Sammy?!

1167
01:42:25,528 --> 01:42:28,948
You tell everybody about Sammy!
Everybody who'll listen!

1168
01:42:29,032 --> 01:42:31,159
''Remember Sammy Jankis?''
''Remember Sammy Jankis?''

1169
01:42:31,201 --> 01:42:34,162
Great story.
Gets better every time you tell it.

1170
01:42:34,371 --> 01:42:38,333
So you lie to yourself to be happy.
There's nothing wrong with that.

1171
01:42:38,416 --> 01:42:42,295
We all do it. Who cares if there's a few
little details you'd rather not remember?

1172
01:42:43,671 --> 01:42:47,092
- What the fuck are you talking about?
- l don't know.

1173
01:42:47,175 --> 01:42:52,055
Your wife surviving the assault.
Her not believing your condition.

1174
01:42:52,138 --> 01:42:56,059
The torment and pain and anguish
tearing her up inside.

1175
01:42:57,394 --> 01:42:58,645
The insulin.

1176
01:42:59,896 --> 01:43:02,691
That's Sammy, not me.
l told you about Sammy.

1177
01:43:02,774 --> 01:43:05,819
Yeah, right.
Like you tell yourself over and over again.

1178
01:43:05,902 --> 01:43:09,364
Conditioning yourself to remember,
learning through repetition.

1179
01:43:09,406 --> 01:43:12,283
Sammy let his wife kill herself.
Sammy ended up in an institution.

1180
01:43:12,367 --> 01:43:15,662
Sammy was a con man. A faker.

1181
01:43:15,745 --> 01:43:17,956
l never said that Sammy was faking.

1182
01:43:17,997 --> 01:43:20,875
You exposed him for what he was.
A fraud.

1183
01:43:20,959 --> 01:43:23,002
l was wrong. That's the whole point.

1184
01:43:24,212 --> 01:43:27,424
- See, Sammy's wife came to me...
- Sammy didn't have a wife.

1185
01:43:30,135 --> 01:43:33,013
It was your wife who had diabetes.

1186
01:43:38,893 --> 01:43:39,894
Ouch!

1187
01:43:42,022 --> 01:43:44,190
My wife wasn't diabetic.

1188
01:43:44,899 --> 01:43:46,943
You sure?

1189
01:43:51,448 --> 01:43:53,408
Ouch! Cut it out!

1190
01:43:53,491 --> 01:43:55,535
She wasn't diabetic.

1191
01:43:55,618 --> 01:43:59,330
You think l don't know my own wife?
What the fuck is wrong with you?

1192
01:43:59,414 --> 01:44:02,542
l guess l can only make you remember
the things you want to be true.

1193
01:44:02,542 --> 01:44:05,295
- Like old Jimmy down there.
- He's not the right guy.

1194
01:44:05,378 --> 01:44:07,547
He was to you.

1195
01:44:07,630 --> 01:44:10,967
Come on, you got your revenge.
